{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require airlines to allow name changes if a passenger can\u2019t travel",
        "additional_details": "Some airlines don\u2019t allow name changes or refunds. If someone is unable to fly, they may have to buy new tickets. We think this is unfair, especially for some families who may face high costs during school holidays potentially to avoid term-time absence fines. We believe it may affect low-income families hardest. We think if the seat will still be used, it\u2019s reasonable to allow a name change or refund. We would allow airlines to charge a fair fee to cover admin costs, balancing consumer rights with business needs. ",
        "background": "Require UK airlines to allow name changes on tickets or refunds if a passenger can\u2019t travel. We think airlines should not force some people to buy new tickets when plans change unexpectedly.",
